		<h2 class="top-story-header ">
			<a class="story" rel="published-1291310588802" href="/web/20101203045420/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-11886943">&#039;New form of life&#039; loves arsenic<img src="/web/20101203045420im_/http://news.bbcimg.co.uk/media/images/50235000/jpg/_50235737_wolfesimon3hrrgb.jpg" alt="Halomonadaceae bacteria (Science)" /></a>
		</h2>

	   	
	   	<p>A bacterium that uses arsenic in place of phosphorus breaks a golden rule of life on Earth, widening the scope of a hunt for life on other planets. 	</p>
